<p>From my android application class, I want to create a libGdx Sprite and return it from a function. I'm using following code for it : </p>  <pre><code>public Sprite getSprite() {      Sprite sp = new Sprite();      Gdx.app.postRunnable(new Runnable() {          @Override         public void run() {           Texture tex = new Texture(_bitmap.getWidth(), _bitmap.getHeight(), Format.RGBA8888);           GLES20.glBindTexture(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D, tex.getTextureObjectHandle());           GLUtils.texImage2D(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, _heroBitmap, 0);           GLES20.glBindTexture(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0);           _bitmap.recycle();            sp.setTexture(tex);  // error is here         }          });      return sp; } </code></pre>  <p>If I don't use separate thread for creating Texture , app Crashes.</p>  <p>I take help from <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14930463/converting-android-bitmap-to-libgdxs-texture">here</a></p>  <p>to covert bitmap into libGdx texture.</p>